21
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:25,460
So let's continue on this path and go a little bit more in depth
让我们沿着这个理念再深入一点

22
00:02:25,700 --> 00:02:29,110
into this idea of self-concordance.
探讨一下自我和谐

23
00:02:35,830 --> 00:02:38,640
What are some benefits of self-concordance?
自我和谐有什么好处呢

24
00:02:38,840 --> 00:02:39,650
The first one-
自我和谐

25
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:42,850
and there are many- the first one is the obvious one.
有很多好处 其中第一点非常显而易见

26
00:02:43,120 --> 00:02:45,390
You don't need to be a rocket scientist
你不需要成为一个火箭科学家

27
00:02:45,630 --> 00:02:48,630
or even a social scientist to understand that
或者社会科学家 就能理解

28
00:02:48,870 --> 00:02:53,320
setting self-concordant goals can potentially make us happier.
制定自我和谐的目标可以让我们更快乐

29
00:02:53,870 --> 00:02:56,480
Because we are pursuing something we care about,
因为我们在追求自己在意的事

30
00:02:56,740 --> 00:03:01,980
it is more likely to reinforce our enjoyment of the journey.
更加增加了人生旅途的乐趣

31
00:03:03,410 --> 00:03:06,380
The second thing,in addition to increasing well being,
第二 除了增加幸福感

32
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:09,960
certainly connected to well being is that very often,
当然也跟幸福感紧密相关的是

33
00:03:10,200 --> 00:03:12,910
having self-concordant goals- having goals in general,
制定自我和谐的目标 整体上制定目标

34
00:03:13,140 --> 00:03:15,600
but in particular self-concordant goals,
但特别制定一些自我和谐的目标

35
00:03:15,850 --> 00:03:17,490
resolves internal conflicts.
能解决内在的心理冲突

36
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:20,580
For example- it helps us deal with anxiety,
比如说 它可以帮我们解决焦虑

37
00:03:20,830 --> 00:03:24,110
with uncertainty,with existential questions-
解决疑惑 解决有关存在的问题

38
00:03:24,330 --> 00:03:27,650
"What am I about? What am I doing? Why am I here?"
"我是谁 我在干什么 我为什么在这儿"

39
00:03:28,170 --> 00:03:31,480
And if you think about it,very often when we go through periods
如果你思考这些 通常是在那种

40
00:03:31,660 --> 00:03:33,950
when we are not sure where we are going,
我们不确定该走向何方

41
00:03:34,530 --> 00:03:40,920
where every fork in the road is about ambivalence and uncertainty
站在十字路口 前路迷雾重重的时候

42
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:43,940
that's when existential questions come up.
这就是有关存在的问题出现的时候

43
00:03:45,570 --> 00:03:48,080
That's when there's uncertainty.
这就是犹豫出现的时候

44
00:03:48,370 --> 00:03:50,620
That's when very often,there's unhappiness,
这就是不快乐出现的时候

45
00:03:50,860 --> 00:03:53,100
whereas when we know what our path is,
如果我们知道我们该往哪儿走

46
00:03:53,340 --> 00:03:55,390
it helps to resolve internal conflict.
就不会有那么多的内在心理冲突

47
00:03:57,270 --> 00:03:58,910
An interesting way to think about it
我们可以从一个很有趣的角度来看它

48
00:03:59,130 --> 00:04:04,110
is by drawing comparison to interpersonal conflicts.
也就是将它与人际间的冲突相对比

49
00:04:04,340 --> 00:04:08,770
So here we are talking about intra-personal conflicts- within:
我们现在讲的是人的内在冲突 是心理内在的

50
00:04:09,040 --> 00:04:11,780
anxiety,depression- often a result of that.
焦虑 沮丧 通常会造成类似的后果

51
00:04:12,070 --> 00:04:15,330
But there's a lot of research on interpersonal conflicts.
有很多关于人际间冲突的研究

52
00:04:15,570 --> 00:04:17,000
And I talked about briefly
我在讲到实践唯心主义

53
00:04:17,230 --> 00:04:24,600
when I discussed practical idealism and conflict resolution.
以及冲突的解决时简单讲过

54
00:04:25,020 --> 00:04:26,570
And the way to deal with the conflicts,
面对冲突的办法

55
00:04:26,790 --> 00:04:29,000
the best way to deal with the conflicts and resolve them
面对并解决冲突的最好办法

56
00:04:29,270 --> 00:04:31,580
is to have a super ordinate goal,
就是制定一个协调的目标

57
00:04:31,830 --> 00:04:37,370
a goal in which both sides- both conflicting sides engage in
使得冲突的双方都参与其中

58
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:41,410
and are dependent on one another or intra-dependent.
并内在地相互依赖

59
00:04:41,980 --> 00:04:46,960
And that resolves interpersonal or intergroup conflicts.
这样就能够解决人际间或组织间的冲突

60
00:04:47,230 --> 00:04:50,590
This is work of Muzafer Sherif or Elliot Aronson.
这是Muzafer Sherif或Elliot Aronson所做的研究

61
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:57,000
In the same way,having a goal helps to solve internal conflicts,
同理 制定目标有助于解决内在冲突

62
00:04:57,250 --> 00:04:59,180
intra-personal conflicts.
人内在的心理冲突

63
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:04,020
Because it takes our mind away from those existential,
因为它能让我们暂时忘却那些关于存在的

64
00:05:04,270 --> 00:05:07,360
often important,but sometimes difficult questions,
很重要 但通常很难的问题

65
00:05:07,620 --> 00:05:09,270
especially when they persist.
尤其是不断出现时

66
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:11,780
Away from anxiety.Away from depression.
它能使我们远离焦虑 远离沮丧

67
00:05:12,050 --> 00:05:16,020
And we are focused on something we really,really want to do.
我们能集中精力于我们十分想做的事

68
00:05:19,210 --> 00:05:24,210
Also,it increases the likelihood of success.
同时 它还增加了成功的可能性

69
00:05:26,090 --> 00:05:30,140
Individuals who set self-concordant goals are more motivated-
制定了自我和谐目标的人会更有动力

70
00:05:30,410 --> 00:05:32,040
they are more likely to work hard.
他们会更努力地工作

71
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:34,210
They are more likely to put their all in-
他们会全身心地投入到

72
00:05:34,430 --> 00:05:35,980
whatever it is- that they are doing.
他们所做的事中去

73
00:05:36,220 --> 00:05:37,210
In the long term,
从长远来看

74
00:05:37,470 --> 00:05:40,540
those who pursue their passions are more likely to succeed.
那些追求自己热爱事业的人都更容易取得成功

75
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,440
Again,seems pretty straight forward,
这似乎非常直白

76
00:05:43,660 --> 00:05:45,650
pretty self-evident common sense.
显而易见 简直是常识

77
00:05:46,050 --> 00:05:49,290
But as we often said,common sense is not that common.
但我们常说 常识也并不是那么显而易见的

78
00:05:49,550 --> 00:05:51,240
In many ways,
很大程度上说

79
00:05:51,490 --> 00:05:55,570
this increased likelihood of success when we pursue the things
这种在我们追求自己热爱的事业时

80
00:05:55,800 --> 00:06:02,030
that we are passionate about defines the "no pain,no gain" maxim
成功的可能性的增加 重新定义了"不劳无获"的公理

81
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:10,600
It defines it and changes it to the following maxim:
它将其重新定义为如下定理

82
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:13,030
"Do it better with pleasure."
"愉悦劳作则多获"

83
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:18,480
Now if you quote me on this,I'll deny it.
如果你要引用 我会否认我说过

84
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:21,330
If you show someone the video of me saying it,
如果你给别人看我说这句话的录像

85
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:25,560
I'll say that it's my cheesy twin brother who coined it.
我会说这是我的双胞胎兄弟

86
00:06:26,060 --> 00:06:27,500
But it's true.
但确实是这样

87
00:06:27,730 --> 00:06:32,340
We do do it better with pleasure if we pursue our passions.
如果我们热爱这项事业 就确实能把它做得更好

88
00:06:33,870 --> 00:06:36,760
What happens in practice- again,there's a lot of research on it.
在实际生活中 同样也有很多关于这个的研究

89
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:40,300
You are reading some of it; I elaborate on some of it in the book
你们读到了一些 我把某些研究编进了书里

90
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:42,030
There's a lot of research that shows that
有很多研究显示

91
00:06:42,230 --> 00:06:46,480
when we are engaged in a self-concordant goal,
当我们沉浸于自我和谐的目标时

92
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:48,360
we are much more likely
就会更倾向于

93
00:06:48,610 --> 00:06:52,840
to then continue to pursue self-concordant goals.
继续追求其他自我和谐的目标

94
00:06:53,220 --> 00:06:57,590
Because it was good that we were more successful;
因为这样很好 我们更成功了

95
00:06:57,850 --> 00:07:00,450
we want more of it.It's self-reinforcing.
我们还不满足 这叫做自我强化

96
00:07:00,690 --> 00:07:05,320
Not just on the macro level of life goals where it does that,
不仅是从生活目标的宏观角度来讲是这样

97
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:09,910
but also on the micro level.And what we see is a trickle effect.
微观角度也是这样 这其实是种涓滴效应

98
00:07:10,140 --> 00:07:14,790
People who set self-concordant goals were actually doing better
制定了自我和谐目标的人其实

99
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:19,390
in areas that were not necessarily self-concordant.
在非自我和谐的方面也做得更好了

100
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:21,230
For instance-
打个比方

101
00:07:21,440 --> 00:07:28,140
let's say you are a member of an undergrad A ccapella group.
比如说你是一个大学生合唱团的成员

102
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:31,220
And you really enjoy it.
你很喜欢这件事

103
00:07:31,450 --> 00:07:33,940
In self-concordant,it's something that you believe in.
从自我和谐的角度来看 这是你所信仰的事

104
00:07:34,170 --> 00:07:36,950
Something you enjoy.Something that is interesting to you.
是你喜欢的事 是你感兴趣的事

105
00:07:37,220 --> 00:07:38,050
Something you are doing
是一件你正在做

106
00:07:38,240 --> 00:07:40,800
because you are really want to be doing it.
因为你确实非常想做的事

107
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:44,980
In other words,a self-concordant goal that will have an effect,
换句话说 自我和谐的目标会对你生活的

108
00:07:45,210 --> 00:07:48,040
a positive effect on other areas in your life-
其他方面产生积极影响

109
00:07:48,790 --> 00:07:52,160
such as a class that you don't necessarily enjoy that much,
比如说一门你不那么喜欢的课

110
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:55,080
but you are doing more because you feel that you have to,
你去上课是因为你觉得你必须要去

111
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:58,140
as opposed to you really really want to.
而不是你真的非常想去

112
00:07:59,770 --> 00:08:01,670
So potentially identifying self-concordant goals
因此找到自我和谐的目标

113
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:04,440
can also help you improve your grades.
其实可以帮助你提高成绩

114
00:08:04,810 --> 00:08:07,360
Again,even though they are not related at all.
虽然它们似乎毫不相关

115
00:08:07,960 --> 00:08:11,640
Because overall,you are more motivated; you are more excited;
因为总体来说 你更有动力了 你更兴奋了

116
00:08:11,880 --> 00:08:13,490
you are more interested; and you enjoy life
你更感兴趣了 你用更积极的感情

117
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:17,050
as a whole more in positive emotions have a trickle effect.
来享受整个人生 这就是涓滴效应

118
00:08:17,280 --> 00:08:21,020
In a way you can think about it like a candle in a dark room.
这个效应可以想象为黑暗房间里的蜡烛

119
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:24,260
Very often you don't need to light up the entire room with lights
通常你不需要将点很多灯照亮整个屋子

120
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:26,570
A single candle sometimes
有时只需一根蜡烛

121
00:08:26,780 --> 00:08:31,160
is enough to spread the light to darkened corners of the room.
就足以将光明遍布房间每一个角落

122
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:32,900
The same with the self-concordant goals.
自我和谐的目标也是这样

123
00:08:33,130 --> 00:08:39,520
They have a trickle effect.Choosing to do things-
它们具有涓滴效应

124
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:45,250
doing what we want to do has also health benefits.
选择做我们想做的事同样对健康也有好处

125
00:08:45,480 --> 00:08:47,330
This is one of the most important studies done
这是心理学领域的重要研究之一

126
00:08:47,540 --> 00:08:52,880
in the field of psychology by,once again,our own Ellen Langer.
同样是由我们学校的Ellen Langer做的研究

127
00:08:53,540 --> 00:08:58,720
What she did was going into old age homes and divide it-
她所做的就是去了一个养老院

128
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:02,160
the old age home randomly into two groups.
将老人们随机分为两组

129
00:09:02,870 --> 00:09:07,350
The one group got all the support that they needed-
第一组所有需要都能得到满足

130
00:09:07,620 --> 00:09:10,000
whatever they wanted they got.
不管什么需要都能满足

131
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,730
They asked for certain food- they got it.
他们想吃什么 就能吃什么

132
00:09:11,970 --> 00:09:15,940
They asked to be helped,carrying out certain tasks- they got it.
他们想在某些事情上寻求帮助 同样也能满足

133
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:18,530
Everything was done for them.
所有事情都无需他们动手

134
00:09:18,780 --> 00:09:22,510
In many ways,the old age homes that many people dream of.
很大程度上来说 这是大多数人梦想的养老院

135
00:09:24,090 --> 00:09:27,700
And then the second group didn't have as good.
而第二组就没有这么好的待遇了

136
00:09:28,050 --> 00:09:29,430
Not everything was catered for them.
他们不能衣来伸手饭来张口

137
00:09:29,650 --> 00:09:32,090
They very often had to do their own things.
时常都需要自己动手

138
00:09:32,290 --> 00:09:35,930
For example,notably,they had to water their own plants.
比如说 他们必须自己浇花

139
00:09:36,940 --> 00:09:40,610
They very often had to set their own routine during the day.
他们必须自己规划每天做的事

140
00:09:40,850 --> 00:09:46,220
The service wasn't as great as the first group.
服务没有第一组那么周到

141
00:09:46,770 --> 00:09:52,300
They had to tell the employees if they needed something.
他们需要什么的话 必须自己告诉职员

142
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:54,630
They very often had to get it themselves.
经常需要自己动手丰衣足食

143
00:09:56,220 --> 00:10:00,880
And again,they planted- they watered their own plants.
同样 他们需要自己浇花

144
00:10:01,130 --> 00:10:01,930
And what they did was-
而研究的内容是

145
00:10:02,140 --> 00:10:05,960
Langer created this two different scenarios
Langer创造了这两种不同的情境

146
00:10:06,190 --> 00:10:09,480
and then went back 18 months later.
然后一年半后再回来

147
00:10:09,730 --> 00:10:12,210
After 18 months,the second group,
一年半后 第二组

148
00:10:12,430 --> 00:10:14,330
the group that watered their plants,
自己浇花的那一组

149
00:10:14,540 --> 00:10:17,520
the group that took care of their day,
自己照顾自己的那一组

150
00:10:17,730 --> 00:10:19,720
the group that was not catered for,
没有人管顾的那一组

151
00:10:19,940 --> 00:10:24,290
in the same way as the first group-
跟第一组相比起来

152
00:10:25,810 --> 00:10:31,420
they were less likely to be depressed; they were happier;
他们没那么沮丧 他们更快乐

153
00:10:31,630 --> 00:10:38,920
they were more energetic; more independent,physically healthier.
他们更有活力 更独立 也更健康

154
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:40,070
And the clincher:
更关键的是

155
00:10:40,290 --> 00:10:48,000
18 months later,they were 50 percent more likely to be alive.
一年半后 他们活着的比例比另一组高出一半

156
00:10:49,470 --> 00:10:53,270
The only difference being that group that was healthier,happier,
唯一的区别就在于更健康 更开心

157
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:56,450
more likely to be alive,had choice.
更高存活率的这组 有选择的权利

158
00:10:56,660 --> 00:10:58,330
They did their own thing.
他们能做自己想做的事

159
00:11:00,010 --> 00:11:01,310
They were asked what do you want to do,
他们会询问自己想做什么

160
00:11:01,580 --> 00:11:06,310
as opposed to being catered for,being supported.
而不是衣来伸手饭来张口

161
00:11:07,370 --> 00:11:13,100
And in some way,this was too easy.There was no choice involved.
从某种角度来说 这太轻松了 不需要做什么选择

162
00:11:13,370 --> 00:11:15,280
And when we choose,when we do what we want to,
当我们能够选择时 当我们做自己想做的事时

163
