when we talked about the research with at risk population.
我们在讲到关于危险人群的研究时说过

1046
01:07:03,140 --> 01:07:05,980
Just like Marva Collins asked a different question.
就像Marva Collins曾经问过一个不一样的问题

1047
01:07:06,240 --> 01:07:09,190
Because questions open up avenues,
因为问题能打开思路

1048
01:07:09,440 --> 01:07:11,830
quests that we may have not seen before.
探索我们之前可能没有见过的东西

1049
01:07:12,080 --> 01:07:15,740
And the question became "what do those who were successful
这样问题就变成"那些成功的

1050
01:07:16,010 --> 01:07:19,830
and able to lead a healthy and happy life do?"
过着健康快乐生活的人是怎么做的"

1051
01:07:20,480 --> 01:07:22,430
In other words,focusing on what works.
换句话说 关注起作用的事物

1052
01:07:22,660 --> 01:07:25,150
In other words,focusing on tip of the stem.
也就是关注茎尖端的芽

1053
01:07:25,420 --> 01:07:29,540
Because while most people are stressed,not all of them are.
因为虽然很多人都压力过大 但不是所有人都这样

1054
01:07:29,760 --> 01:07:33,840
There are people who are able to be successful
有一些人能够很成功

1055
01:07:34,080 --> 01:07:37,160
and at the same time,lead a health and happy life.
同时过着健康和快乐的生活

1056
01:07:37,410 --> 01:07:43,770
What do they do? What is it about them? Here is what they do.
他们是怎么做的 他们做了些什么 他们是这样做的

1057
01:07:44,020 --> 01:07:44,860
What was found was that
人们发现

1058
01:07:45,060 --> 01:07:48,720
there are some distinguishing characteristics- two of them:
他们有一些特别的特质 有两点

1059
01:07:49,150 --> 01:07:51,400
they set rituals for themselves
他们为自己建立例行公事

1060
01:07:51,640 --> 01:07:54,130
and we talked about rituals in the past;
我们之前讲过例行公事的

1061
01:07:54,490 --> 01:07:56,440
the second thing that they do-
第二件事

1062
01:07:56,680 --> 01:07:58,540
and this is what I'm going to elaborate on now-
也就是我现在要详细讲的

1063
01:07:58,780 --> 01:08:02,000
the second thing that they do,in addition to having rituals,
他们所做的第二件事 除了建立例行公事

1064
01:08:02,380 --> 01:08:03,450
whether it's a lot of rituals,
不管是很多的例行公事

1065
01:08:03,650 --> 01:08:06,840
or few rituals,depending on individual needs and differences.
还是寥寥几件 视乎个人需要和个人差异

1066
01:08:07,090 --> 01:08:08,470
In addition to setting rituals,
除了建立例行公事

1067
01:08:08,730 --> 01:08:14,790
they particularly set rituals for both work and for recovery.
他们还特别地不仅为工作 还为恢复也建立了例行公事

1068
01:08:15,420 --> 01:08:18,070
Let me explain.Let me explain.
让我来解释一下 解释一下

1069
01:08:20,120 --> 01:08:21,320
What I'm going to say now
我现在要说的是

1070
01:08:21,330 --> 01:08:23,300
is some thing that psychologists did not see before,
心理学家以前没有意识到的

1071
01:08:23,530 --> 01:08:25,870
because it was hidden just like the children on the bus
因为它就像公车上的孩子一样隐藏着

1072
01:08:26,100 --> 01:08:28,800
or hidden by the first question.
或者被第一个问题掩盖着

1073
01:08:29,130 --> 01:08:31,380
It was only after asking the second question
只有问了第二个问题

1074
01:08:31,720 --> 01:08:33,540
that they notice this.
他们才会注意到

1075
01:08:34,730 --> 01:08:39,660
What they noticed was that these individuals ritualize work
他们注意到这些人将工作和恢复

1076
01:08:39,890 --> 01:08:41,950
and recovery and in essence what they found-
例行公事化 本质上他们发现的是

1077
01:08:42,180 --> 01:08:46,040
this is the most surprising result in my mind in studying stress-
这是我觉得研究压力时所得的最惊人的结果

1078
01:08:46,450 --> 01:08:49,960
is that stress was actually not the problem.
那就是问题其实不在于压力

1079
01:08:50,220 --> 01:08:52,200
We were looking in the wrong place.
我们找错了地方

1080
01:08:52,780 --> 01:08:58,200
In fact,what they found was stress was good for us!
事实上他们发现压力对我们是有好处的

1081
01:08:58,460 --> 01:09:01,040
That stress actually cultivated resilience,
压力实际上培养了我们的忍耐性

1082
01:09:01,360 --> 01:09:05,560
strength and helped us be happier in the long run.
力量 并且从长远来讲让我们更快乐

1083
01:09:05,840 --> 01:09:06,690
Wait a minute.
稍等片刻

1084
01:09:06,900 --> 01:09:09,310
What does that mean? Well,think about the following analogy.
这是什么意思呢 想想下面这个类比

1085
01:09:09,740 --> 01:09:11,630
Think about the physical realm.
想想运动方面

1086
01:09:11,910 --> 01:09:12,600
What happens to you,
你发生了什么

1087
01:09:12,850 --> 01:09:15,480
what actually happens to you when you go to the gym?
你去健身房时实际上发生了什么呢

1088
01:09:15,790 --> 01:09:19,580
when you go to the gym,you lift weights.
当你去健身房 你举重时

1089
01:09:20,300 --> 01:09:23,580
What are you doing to your muscle? You are stressing your muscle!
你对你的肌肉做了什么 你在给你的肌肉压力!

1090
01:09:23,840 --> 01:09:24,780
In fact,
事实上

1091
01:09:25,030 --> 01:09:29,090
you are carrying part of the- there are micro tears in your cells.
你其实就在... 你的细胞在偷偷流泪

1092
01:09:29,820 --> 01:09:33,210
Now is this a bad thing? That you are doing that?
请问这是坏事吗 你所做的事是坏事吗

1093
01:09:33,920 --> 01:09:35,170
Not at all! It's a good thing.
完全不是 这是件好事

1094
01:09:35,420 --> 01:09:37,740
Because you lift weights and then two days later,
因为你举重 然后两天之后

1095
01:09:38,180 --> 01:09:40,420
you lift these weights again.
再去举重

1096
01:09:40,750 --> 01:09:43,670
And the next week,you continue lifting these weights.
然后下周 你接着举重

1097
01:09:44,000 --> 01:09:44,780
And on and on.
长此以往

1098
01:09:44,980 --> 01:09:48,250
You do it for a month and two and four months and six months.
你举了一个月 两个月 四个 六个月

1099
01:09:48,510 --> 01:09:52,290
And after a year of lifting weights,you begin to look like me!
然后举了一年的重之后 你就会像我一样

1100
01:09:53,940 --> 01:10:00,860
Or maybe not.So the stress part is actually good for us.
或者也不会 所以压力其实对我们是有好处的

1101
01:10:01,140 --> 01:10:02,190
What's the problem though?
那真正的问题是什么呢

1102
01:10:02,410 --> 01:10:06,940
When do the problems begin with stressing those muscles?
比如说压缩肌肉时 问题是从什么时候开始的呢

1103
01:10:08,130 --> 01:10:11,690
It's when you lift weights,and a minute later,
是你去举重 然后一分钟之后

1104
01:10:11,950 --> 01:10:13,610
you lift the same weights again,
你又去举重

1105
01:10:13,920 --> 01:10:17,950
and again,and again,and again,and so on and so on.
然后不断举 不断举 不断不断地举

1106
01:10:18,170 --> 01:10:19,730
What would happen to you then,
然后会发生的事就是

1107
01:10:19,980 --> 01:10:23,700
if you don't take a break,whether it's a break between sessions,
如果你不休息 不管是运动之间的休息

1108
01:10:23,940 --> 01:10:27,540
whether it's break,days break? What happens to you then?
或者是休息几天 那么会发生什么呢

1109
01:10:28,500 --> 01:10:31,650
That's when you get injured.That's when you get hurt.
你就会受伤 到时你就会受伤

1110
01:10:31,880 --> 01:10:34,600
That's when you actually tear or pull a muscle.
那时你的肌肉就会拉伤

1111
01:10:34,970 --> 01:10:36,780
That's when you become over-worked-
那时你就会锻炼过度

1112
01:10:37,040 --> 01:10:39,970
and that has psychological as well as physical effects.
这既有生理上 也有心理上的影响

1113
01:10:40,320 --> 01:10:42,320
That's when you are over-trained.
这时候你就是锻炼过度了

1114
01:10:42,580 --> 01:10:44,490
In other words,the problem is not stress,
换言之 问题不在于压力

1115
01:10:44,700 --> 01:10:47,640
not on the physical level,nor on the psychological level.
不是生理上的问题 也不是心理上的问题

1116
01:10:47,840 --> 01:10:50,900
The problem is lack of recovery.
问题在于缺少恢复

1117
01:10:52,060 --> 01:10:56,950
Individuals who are both successful,happy,thriving,
那些既成功又快乐幸福的人

1118
01:10:57,170 --> 01:11:02,270
flourishing are ones who do experience stress.
是会感受到压力的

1119
01:11:02,990 --> 01:11:06,950
However,they also pay very close attention to recovery.
然而他们很注重恢复

1120
01:11:07,970 --> 01:11:11,090
Just like any athlete here in this room knows that
就好像在座的任何运动员都知道

1121
01:11:11,320 --> 01:11:14,650
you have tapering,you have time-off before important games.
你们会有调整期 在重要比赛前都会有休息

1122
01:11:15,750 --> 01:11:19,260
You don't lift the same weights day in and day out.
你们不会每天去举重

1123
01:11:21,110 --> 01:11:23,640
The same thing on the psychological level.
从心理层面上讲也是这样

1124
01:11:23,910 --> 01:11:25,960
If we don't take breaks,
如果我们不懂得休息

1125
01:11:26,390 --> 01:11:29,330
we will pay a price- on the physical level,we get injured;
我们会付出代价 在生理层面上 我们会受伤

1126
01:11:29,550 --> 01:11:31,320
on the psychological level,
在心理层面上

1127
01:11:31,580 --> 01:11:35,950
we experience anxiety,ultimately,potentially depression.
我们会感觉到焦虑 最终可能导致抑郁

1128
01:11:38,450 --> 01:11:40,350
Stress is fine.It's good.
压力没有关系 它是好事

1129
01:11:40,590 --> 01:11:44,910
